definition.value: A young bird.
A newly hatched animal.
A mature female chicken that is kept for laying eggs.
A turkey that is kept for laying eggs.
A young hen, especially the one less than one-year-old.
Less than one year old or is part of a flock where no eggs have yet been laid.
A mature male turkey, that is usually two years old or more.
An adult male sheep that is kept for breeding and wool production.
A castrated male sheep.
A leaf or seed of a dill plant (Anethum graveolens), that is used as a spice for flavouring food.
A cutlet made from chicken breast.
A food datum indicating that a no food preservation process is planned for one or more food items.
A meal that is a co-product produced after the extraction of oil from the seed of the Ethiopian mustard plant (Brassica carinata).
A mint food product which is a sauce made from finely chopped spearmint (Mentha spicata) leaves soaked in vinegar, and a sweetener.
A liquid which is at its boiling point under given atmospheric conditions.
A material processing in which a liquid gains heat.
A heating liquid process at the end of which a liquid begins to boil.
A heating liquid to boiling point process in which water begins to boil.
A fish that has not reached to sexual maturity.
A fish that is recently hatched and has reached the stage where its yolk-sac has almost disappeared and its swim bladder is operational to the point where the fish can actively feed for itself.
An egg or spawn of a fish that is contained within or separated from the ovary.
A food product which is prepared in an Italian cooking style.
An ingredient that is used in the preparation of animal feed.
A formula mixture of micronutrients that is used as a component in compound feed.
A compound feed premix in which medicinal substances has been added.
Food material which can be used to meet nutritional requirements of animals, particularly livestock such as cattle, goats, sheep, horses, chickens and pigs.
This is the replacement term for ENVO "animal feed" (ENVO_02000047)
An aggregate of rice kernels.
Rice is a somewhat ambiguous term that allows white, brown, black etc. varietals in various stages of processing.
A piece or pieces or amount of substance derived from one or more organisms.
A rice kernel which is attached to its husk.
A husk of a rice kernel.
Anatomical or other piece(s) or substance derived from one or more plants.
A severed part of an animal.
An anatomical or other piece derived from a plant.
One or more pieces of animals.
A piece or pieces or amount of substance derived from one or more fungai.
A smaller cut of meat that is obtained from the larger primal cut of an animal.
An animal meat cut that is derived from a sub-primal, individual muscle cut or minor primal cut.
A food product that is derived from some ostrich.
A food product that derives from a guar plant.
A specific set of food items that are served together during a meal, all at the same time.
A whole mafurra nut.
A food product made with romano cheese
A boiled whole potato.
A pulp made from avocado flesh.
A cooked spelt kernel.
A characteristic of organism(s) or pieces(s) thereof, which have not had material processing that affects its biochemical composition.
A whole raw sprouted navy bean.
